## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for housing.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers housing visibility,
occupancy-aware display,
access-aware surfaces,
placement-aware state display,
and safe failure rendering.

## current_view_state
Runtime-visible housing state must distinguish:
- active occupied housing
- restricted housing
- partially occupied housing
- historical housing
- closed housing

## validation_rules
- housing identity must resolve
- occupancy scope must resolve
- actor access scope must resolve
- placement scope must be valid
- disclosure scope must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid housing identity
- invalid occupancy basis
- invalid access scope
- invalid placement scope
- safe runtime fallback

## observability
Runtime must emit enough signals
to distinguish housing state,
occupancy state,
access result,
placement result,
and failure surface.

## review_checklist
- housing runtime scope is explicit
- access-aware rendering is explicit
- failure handling is explicit
